OL,3,CPothole plague: frustrated motorists
OL,4,Ccall for long-term repairs to damaged
OL,5,Croads
OL,7,FOne repair shop mechanic near Reading
OL,8,Fsays he's constantly having to deal
OL,9,Fwith damaged vehicles, and he's been
OL,10,Fleft #200 out of pocket after his own
OL,11,Fcar was damaged when he hit a pothole.
OL,13,FAnd another garage shop at
OL,14,FWaterlooville near Portsmouth is
OL,15,Ffocusing solely on repairing damaged
OL,16,Ftyres. Paul O'Neil said it means they
OL,17,Fcan't get on with other work.
