OL,3,CPothole plague: frustrated motorists
OL,4,Ccall for long-term repairs to damaged
OL,5,Croads
OL,7,FThe Basingstoke-based AA motoring
OL,8,Forganisation has released figures
OL,9,Fshowing they were called to more than
OL,10,Fhalf a million pothole-related
OL,11,Fincidents last year. AA President
OL,12,FEdmund King supports the move and
OL,13,Fsaid: "If a pothole reappears within
OL,14,Ffive years, it would be repaired for
OL,15,Ffree of charge under the warranty.
OL,17,F"This proposal has the potential to
OL,18,Fsave money for council tax payers but
OL,19,Fmore importantly, ensure the pothole
OL,20,Fis repaired correctly first time."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
